We are using a custom authenticator that integrates with Internet2's Shibboleth SSO. Because of this the top Hot Referrer on every page's info is shibboleth (which is a different host than the confluence server).

The scary part about this is that there is a link called "ban" on the hot referrers page that if clicked could essentially keep everyone at our university from hitting that page anymore.

It would be very helpful to either have a list of hosts which are "un-bannable" from page info even by administrators in a properties file or similar, or to even better, jhave a list of hosts which will not show up in the Hot Referrers list at all. (Since it isn't helpful to know that shibboleth is redirecting everyone)

